<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Test Assessment – Polling Required</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body { padding: 40px; max-width: 800px; margin: auto; }
    pre { background: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 6px; overflow-x: auto; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h2 class="mb-4">Assessment Submitted</h2>

  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Status:</strong> The test is being processed asynchronously (202 Accepted).
  </div>

  <p>Your job/ticket has been created. Poll the following URL to check status and retrieve results:</p>

  <div class="input-group mb-3">
    <input type="text" class="form-control" id="pollingUrl" value="<%= polling_url %>" readonly>
    <button class="btn btn-outline-secondary" type="button" onclick="copyToClipboard()">Copy</button>
  </div>

  <p><strong>Manual polling commands:</strong></p>
  <pre>
# Using curl (recommended)
curl -s "<%= polling_url %>" | jq   # pretty-print JSON

# Or just open in browser:
<%= polling_url %>
  </pre>

  <p>Keep refreshing/polling until you see a final result (usually status "completed" or direct FTR JSON-LD with `@graph`).</p>

  <p><small>Original endpoint: <a href="<%= original_endpoint %>" target="_blank"><%= original_endpoint %></a></small></p>

  <hr>

  <p class="text-muted small mt-4">
    When the result is ready, it should contain the same structure as synchronous responses
    (FTR JSON-LD with TestExecutionActivity, TestResult, etc.).
  </p>

  <script>
    function copyToClipboard() {
      const el = document.getElementById('pollingUrl');
      el.select();
      document.execCommand('copy');
      alert('URL copied to clipboard!');
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>